lead_paragraph: Norbert Hofer of the Freedom Party was in a virtual dead heat with Alexander Van der Bellen, a former Green Party leader, in the presidential election on Sunday.

headline.print_headline: Austrian Far-Right Candidate in Election Deadlock
headline.main: In Austrian Election, Far-Right Candidate Is Deadlocked With Rival

snippet: Norbert Hofer of the Freedom Party was in a virtual dead heat with Alexander Van der Bellen, a former Green Party leader, in the presidential election on Sunday.
abstract: Austrian presidential election is deadlocked, with race between far-right candidate Norbert Hofer and economist Alexander Van der Bellen too close to call; mail-in votes will determine winner.
